== Configuration ==

{{Warning|{{C|iwd}} is a work in process is definitely not ready for prime time computing!}}

==== OpenRC ====

Add the iwd daemon to the default runlevel:

{{RootCmd|rc-update add iwd default}}

Start the iwd daemon now:

{{RootCmd|rc-service iwd start}}



=== Connecting to an access point ===
Use 'iwctl station list' to see what adapters you might be able to use:
<!--T:10-->
{{Cmd|iwctl station list|output=<pre>
                            Devices in Station Mode
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Name                State          Scanning
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  wlan0               disconnected
</pre>}}

<!--T:11-->
Find out the status of your wireless LAN adapter:
{{Cmd|iwctl station wlan0 show|output=<pre>
                                 Station: wlan0
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Settable  Property            Value
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
            Scanning            no
            State               disconnected
</pre>}}
<!--T:12-->
Get your wireless LAN adapter in scanning mode:
{{Cmd|iwctl station wlan0 scan}}
<!--T:13-->
And list -after 10 to 20 seconds- the networks found:
{{Cmd|iwctl station wlan0 get-networks|output=<pre>
                               Available networks
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Network name                    Security  Signal
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    FRITZ!Box 7362 SL               psk       ***
    WLAN-105127                     psk       *
</pre>}}

